&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Accusing the District Police Office, Rajbiraj and Area Police Office of Kanchanpur for protecting the perpetrator, Bachhaa Lal registered a writ of mandamus at the Appellate Court in Rajbiraj.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Bachcha Lal is claiming that Roshan Kumar Mandal, 22, of Praswani9 had attempted to rape his 14-year-old daughter on the night of January 24. He further complained that the District Police Office and the Area Police Office refused the case registration. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;According to the police inspector Rajendra Basnet of Kanchanpur Area Police Office, the case was already resolved by an agreement between two parties.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
