&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Arghakhanchi/November 8
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Family of a 13-year-old girl of Dhakabang9 has filed a complaint of child marriage at the District Police Office stating that Jiban Nepali, 19, of Khilji7 had married the girl. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The family had filed a case on November 2 demanding that the marriage be dismissed. Jiban had married the girl on November 1. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Mother of the girl has demanded action against Jiban saying that he had married an under-age girl. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;According to the law, a marriage would only be legal if the boy has reached the age of 21 and the girl 18. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		 Narayan Bhusal

