		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The District Police Office has arrested a driver on November 7 on charge of trying to rape a female passenger. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Police said that driver Sanjiv Kumar Silwal alias Hari Bahadur of Nalang9 had tried to rape her while heading towards Dhading from Kathmandu. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The victim had filed a case at the DPO stating that Silwal tried to rape her at Ashikhola near Ganesh furniture at Sangkosh3. She said that the driver forcefully took her without stopping at her destination. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;DSP Bikash Raj Khanal said that further investigation was ongoing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
