		 सन्दिप राई&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;Panchthar/November 2
		  Gita Baskota, 30, of Phidim2 has accused that her husband Chakra Prasad Baskota, 28, and his family have threatened to kill her. Saying that his family cut off the drinking water pipe in her home, she urged human rights activists and media persons to help her get justice on November 2.
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The victim said that though she filed a case against her family on October 29, the District Police Office took no action. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;She said that she had to fetch water walking for half an hour after her drinking water pipe was cut off. She further said that his family members repeatedly threatened her and asked shopkeepers not to provide her goods. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inspector Yam Bahadur Paudel said that no immediate legal action was taken as it was a family dispute. &lt;/p&gt;
