&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The girl filed a complaint against the duo on July 3 saying that she was taken to a hotel in Khandbari by Bhote in the pretext of taking a tour where she was raped by him and Karki. They youths were arrested on the same day and a charge of rape was filed against them on July 4.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The girl has been staying in the district headquarters to help her younger siblings with their studies. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In another incident, police filed a case under Public Offence Act against Purna Bahadur Gurung, 20, of Mamling7 on July 6 on charge of misbehaving with Bimala Sherpa, 29, of the same place. Gurung is accused of misbehaving with her on drunken state on July 5. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		 Chhetu Sherpa

Jhapa/June 22
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Police have forwarded a case agasint Gangaram Rai, 58, of Goldhap-3 on June 22 accusing of being involved raping a local woman.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Rai is accused of raping a 40-year-old mentally ill woman in the afternoon of June 21 at her home, informed Sub-Inspector Keshav Katuwal of Birtamod Area Police Office. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The family of the woman filed an FIR against the accused at the Birtamod APO on June 22. Rai was arrested in the morning of June 22. The victim was taken to Mechi Zonal Hospital for the health check up. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		 Arjun Basnet

Rupandehi/June 20
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Butwal Area Police Office has rescued Anju Thapa Gahatraj, 26, staying at Sukhkhanagar in ButwalN.P.10 on June 20 following initiation from the human rights defenders. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A badly bruised Anju had filed a case against her husband Chandraman Gahatraj, 36, at NHRC Office accusing him of sexual violence, mistreatment and battering her. She was rescued from her rented room by the police and human rights defenders following her appeal and was taken to Lumbini Zonal Hospital for treatment. The police also took the accused Chandraman in its custody on the same day. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Anju, hailing from Budikot Chidipani in Palpa had an inter-caste marriage some nine years ago. She informed that she was the third wife of her husband adding her claim that the first wife was forced to walk out of marriage and the second wife committed suicide because of his violent behavior. Chandraman has a 7-year-old daughter from Anju and a 18-year-old son from his early marriage. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;According to the victim, the violence had grown in the later years of the marriage. Quoting the doctors, her relatives informed that she had bruises all over her body including her private parts. She added that her husband used to beat her every day, would cut her hair and prick her private parts, would take her compromising pictures and then add up torture. She was also forced to sign on the divorce paper on June 15.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;She was handed over to her brothers-in-law Raju and Ramesh after they expressed commitment of taking care of her. Accepting that their brother had committed a crime, they also pledge to ensure justice for their sister-in-law. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Police Inspector Rameshwar Karki of Butwal Area Police Office said a discussion would be held between the two sides. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		 Amrit Giri

Sindhupalchowk / June 18
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Anuja Gurung (Shrestha), 19, of Chilankha7 has been arrested for her alleged involvement in human trafficking while she was heading to Kathmandu from Charikot from Khandichaur of Mankha6 on June 17.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Shrestha took a 14-year-old girl of Pangretar VDC to Kathmandu with the intention of selling her on June 12, police said. The relatives of the girl had returned the victim from Kathmandu after they knew that Shrestha was trying to sell the girl. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Family of the victim filed a complaint at Barhabise Area Police Office on June 14.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Preparations are underway to file a case of human trafficking against Shrestha at the district court, Sujan Rajbhandari, Inspector at District Police Office said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		 Natibabu Dhital

Makwanpur / June 17
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Man Bahadur Thokar, 58, of Tistung2 has been arrested for his alleged involvement in selling a woman hailing from Tistung8 twenty-one years ago on June 17. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Thokar has been alleged that he, tempting a 22-year-old Tamang woman currently aged 43 to search for a good job, left her in a house of a couple in Padampokhari VDC in 1991. The woman had been staying at her maternal home following demise of her husband. The couple based at Pantale of Padampokhari VDC took the woman to Mumbai and sold her in a brothel taking IRS 2, 00000. The couple had taken her to India deceiving that they would go for watching a movie in the market. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The victim, who returned Nepal last month staying in an Indian brothel for 21 years, filed a complaint against Thokar with the help of women rights organizations recently.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;She has been staying under the protection of Hetauda based Maiti Nepal. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		 Pratap Bista

Sangkhuwasabha/June 14
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The District Court, Chainpur has fined Purna Prasad Pokhrel, 60, of Khandbari1 Rs 14,500 for marrying a minor. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Pokharel had got married to a 15-year-old  girl of Barhabise2 on May 7, 2012, police said. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;He was arrested on May 12 and filed a case under child marriage on May 21. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The girl’s neighbor Tulasi BK was fined Rs 1,000 for persuading the girl to agree for the marriage. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The court said though the Chapter on Child Marriage of Country Code has a provision of six months of jail term and Rs 10,000 in fine, he was released after considering the situation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		 Chhetu Sherpa

Achham / June 13
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Family of a girl has fined Rs. 100000 to family of Anil Tamrakar, 16 of Hattikot7 for having inter-caste marriage with the girl on June 12. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Anil had inter-caste marriage with Dipa Saud, 15, hailing from ward no 8 of same VDC after love affair on May 20, Tamrakar family said. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The couple run away from the village after the marriage, however, family of the girl took control over the couple from Jayagarh Bazaar, separated Dipa from Anil and beat him up on May 21, Tamrakar family informed. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&quot;Saud family had demanded Rs. 500000, however, we denied providing the amount but the family made us to provide Rs. 100000,&quot; Anil said. &quot;Considering ethnic and social harmony, we agreed to provide Rs. 100000 to Saud family,&quot; Anil's father Nairam Tamrakar said. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Earlier, Saud family had filed a complaint at Thanti Area Police Office and urged to search for the couple after Dipa eloped with Anil on May 20.  But Saud family did not make a contact with police after the family found the couple, the Thanti APO said. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Anil's mother, Bhunti Tamrakar had filed a complaint at Thanti APO saying that Saud family had threatened to kill her family members if Rs. 500000 was not given to the girl's family on May 22. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;After the incident, Saud family got Dipa married with a person of Kuskot VDC and provided the sum taken from Tamrakar family to her as dowry during her marriage, Surat Sunar, a local said. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		 Shivaraj Khatri

Panchthar / June 6
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Six youths have been arrested for gang rape of a woman on June 6.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The arrestees are Surendra Basnet, 30, Dipesh Magar, 18, Subash Khawas, 15, Shiva Magar, 17, Debit Lawar, 16 of Phidim1 and Dipesh Shrestha of Sinam5 of Taplujung, the Panchthar District Police Office said. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The arrestees have been accused for raping a 30-year-old woman of Yangnam2 on June 5 after making her unconscious with the help of a medicine. The victim, who has bruises on her arms, chest and back, has been undergoing treatment at district hospital. Details of the incident will be known after the report of her health checkup is received, the hospital source said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;According to the victim, she was raped while she was asleep. Locals said that she was raped at 10:00 pm. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Investigation on the arrestee is underway, Yam Bahadur Paudel, Inspector at the district police office said. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		 Sandip Rai

Bardiya / June 5
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hari Upadhyay, 41 of Dhadhbar6 has been arrested for allegedly attacking his wife, Sumitra Devi Upadhyay, 21 with a sharp weapon on June 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hari, who was under the influence of alcohol, attacked Sumitra to her neck with the sharp weapon while she had been sleeping in the house in the afternoon on June 3. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Injured Sumitra had treated the wounds in a local medical shop and returned home, however, Hari took her out of house and beat her with batons in the night same day. In the meantime, locals and relatives arrived in the scene and informed police. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A team of police from Bansgadhi Area Police Office arrested Upadhyay on June 4, Arun Kumar Singh, inspector at Bardiya District Police Office said, adding that investigation of the incident is underway by filing a case of attempt to murder against the accused in the district court. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
