Dadeldhura / May 22
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Twenty-two Chhaupadi sheds have been dismantled in an attempt to minimize violence against women at Rajyauda VDC of Attital VDC in the district.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As Rajyauda village is most affected by Chhaupadi system in the Attital VDC, the sheds were dismantled with initiatives of locals from (14 to 20) May, Ratan Kunwar, VDC secretary said on May 22.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A woman during menstruation period and post-partum period is required to stay in Chhaupadi sheds as per the system. Several women staying in Chhaupadi sheds become victims of rape while some died due to snakebites.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Before launching the campaign to dismantle the Chhaupadi sheds, the VDC had made people aware against the ill-practices of the system with posters, pamphlets and interactions by visiting the houses of locals in the village, Kunwar said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There are 150 Chhaupadi sheds at Dhimada village in ward no 8 of Attital VDC and preparation are underway to dismantle the sheds there by making the locals aware about consequences of the system, Kunwar added.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		 Keshab Bohara

Khotang/March 19
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;According to the victim, her neighbor Dhan Bahadur Rai, 48, and his wife Sita threatened to kill her on March 9. Stating that she was unsafe, she filed a complaint at the District Administration Office (DAO) on March 12 and National Human Rights Commission (NHRC) on March 18. The district police office said that they had initiated action following the order of the DAO. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Police said that efforts were underway to hold discussion between the two sides at the Baksila police post. The victim's family said that they were demanding action against the culprits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
