Achham/December 8
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;District Court has sent three people to jail in its decision on the rape case of Suntali Dhami on December 8. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Single Bench of District Court Judge Prakash Kharel convicted head constables Birendra Bam and Karbir Thalal and constable Jagadish Pandey. Bam has been sentenced to six years in jail and fined Rs 100,000 while Thalal and Pandey have been sentenced to three years in jail. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Police constable Dhami had filed a case against her six colleagues accusing them of gang raping her on the day of Vijaya Dashami on September 27, 2009. They were arrested on October 7, 2009 and a case of rape was filed against three of them, now convicted, on November 2, 2009 after being suspended a day earlier. Three other accused Sub-Inspector Dan Singh Bhandari, head constable Biradutta Badu and constable Naribhan Mahatara were released on November 1 saying they were innocent. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Commenting on the verdict, Bam claimed that they were made scapegoat in the incident. Though, Thalal's relatives said they would appeal against the verdict at Appellate Court, Bam said he was not moving the upper court. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		 Shivraj Khatri

&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Family Assault, Evict Woman&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Panchthar/December 7&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dilu Hembya, 30 of Amarpur6 was assaulted and evicted from home by brother of her father-in-law Krishna Prasad Hembya, 58, on December 3. Dilu has filed a case at the district police office on December 5 saying that Krishna had padlocked the house after evicting her from home. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;She also accused Hemba of making away with her Rs 10,000. She has sustained injury to her face, chest and leg.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;She has been living with her 8-year-old daughter after her husband Dhan Bahadur Hembya went missing eight years ago. The victim accused that she was reapeatedly mistreated and assaulted by family members after her husband went missing. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A helper at the local awareness child development centre, Hembya said that she was repeatedly assaulted since five years. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;She is being treated at the Panchthar district hospital. She is taking shelter at the emergency service centre run by women and children office and Phidim cooperative.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Likewise, Khoma Devi Aryal, 30, of Lumphabung5 was injured after her brother –in-law Lilanath Aryal, 29, attacked her on December 1. Her family has admitted her to the district hospital on December 6. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sandip Rai&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Woman Files Rape Case against Brother-in-law&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Humla/December 7&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A 40-year-old woman of Raya8 has filed a case at the district police office Humla on December 6 accusing her brother-in-law of raping her. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Husband of the victim has accused Prem Bahadur Rawal, 30, of raping her on December 3 after making her drunk. The victim had made the incident public on December 4 morning. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Medical test of the victim was held at the district hospital Humla on December 6. Dr. Prakash Pratap Sah of the district hospital said that no evidences were seen in the report as the incident had taken place three days ago. She said that she was attacked in head and thigh after the incident. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;She is undergoing treatment at the district hospital Humla. The police has not arrested the accused yet. Police said that the delay in arresting the accused was due to the distance of the incident site from the district headquarters. The victim was staying alone in the house as her husband is running a shop at Simkot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ramesh Aidi&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Bigamous Husband Beats Wife&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Panchthar/December 6&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Devi Maya Jogi, 37, of Amarpur4 has filed a case against her husband Dhan Bahadur Rai, 38, of Ranitar8 at the district police office (DPO) on December 5. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Stating that Dhan Bahadur married her 12 years ago despite having a first wife, she accused him of frequently assaulting her. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dhan Bahadur has 3 children from her first wife and 3 children from his second wife. She said that Dhan Bahadur left her four years ago after leaving for foreign employment. She added that he suddenly returned back on December 2 and attacked her while she was making a house at Bhaluchok bazaar in Amarpur4. She also accused that he made away with Rs 200,000 which she had lent from her neighbor Laxmi Subedi. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Inspector Gopal Prasad Dhakal of the DPO said that search for the accused was ongoing. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sandip Rai&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Youths Accused of Rape Attempt Released after Paying Fine&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Humla/December 6&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Two youths who were arrested on charge of trying to rape two women have been released after paying fine and treatment cost. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Raju Bhandari, 25, and Prakash Bhandari, 23, of Thehe2 in inebriated condition had attempted to rape Sushila Nepali, 25, and her sister-in-law Aastha Nepali, 23, of Kharpanath8 on December 4. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The two accused were released on December 5 as per the rules of the local village. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Inspector Khadak Bhandari said that they did not take the case forward as the victims requested to make compromise with the accused. Bhandari said that police released the accused after they provided Rs 25,000 to the victims since they had filed a complaint of losing property worth the amount in the incident. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;However, one of the victim Sushila said that they made the compromise following pressure from the villagers. The accused were released after they provided the amount and treatment cost at the police office. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ramesh Aidi&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Man Accused of Killing Wife Made Public &lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Dang/December 3&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;District Police Office, Dang have on December 2 made public Birsharan Chaudhary, 25, of Bayar Batuwa in Ghorahi Municipality-1, whom they arrested on charge of killing his wife. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;According to the police, Chaudhary had beaten his wife Nirmala to death following a domestic dispute in inebriated condition on November 30. He was arrested by the police on December 1. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Police said the investigation into the case had begun. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;em&gt;Shalikram Musafir&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Two Arrested for Alleged Gang Rape&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Kathmandu/November 30&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Police have arrested two persons for their alleged involvement in gang rape of an eighteen-year-old girl in the Capital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The arrestees have been identified as Kedar Prasad Phuyal, 28, of Kathmandu Metropolis-16 and Rajan Shrestha, 28, of Dhapasi-28.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The duo was arrested after family of the victim filed a complaint at Sorhakhutte Police Station on November 29, police said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Saying that they will go for traveling in the city, Shrestha had taken the girl to Thamel-based Seti Dovan Guest House on November 28. He called Phuyal and the duo raped the girl in the Guest House, police said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;em&gt;Raju Paswan    &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Man Gets 11 year in Jail for Raping Girl&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Kailali/November 29&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The district court Kailali has slapped 11 years jail term to Raghubir Singh Thagunna, 55, of Geta8 for raping a 13-year-old visually impaired girl. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A single bench of Justice Bishnu Subedi also gave order to pay Rs 75,000 to the victim as compensation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The girl was a student of special education at the Panchodaya Secondary School in Dhangadhi Municipalilty-5. Principal Yadab Joshi of the school had filed a case against Thagunna at the district police office on June 15. Thagunna was arrested the same day and was charged with rape the next day by police. Medical check up of the victim was held at the Seti Zonal Hospital. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Thagunna had raped the girl after taking her from the school hostel to a hotel in Dhangadhi bazaar on June 1. The incident became public after the victim informed prinicipal Joshi about the incident on June 11.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Thagunna is held in the district jail Kailali.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Rape Attempt of Visually Impaired Girl&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Surkhet/November 28&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ram Prasad Acharya, 42, and working as office assistant at the community eye center run by Nepal Redcross Society Surkhet has attempted to rape a 12-year-old visually impaired girl. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;According to an appeal filed by the victim at the Nepal Blind Association (NBA) Surkhet, Acharya tried to rape her at the hostel for the blind students near buspark in Birendranagar Municipality on November 11. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Chairperson of NBA Surkhet, Maya Prasad Jaisi said that the girl allowed Acharya to sleep in a separate room after he asked her to let her sleep in the hostel saying that the traffic police had not allowed him to go home that night. &quot;But he came to the girl's room in the night and attempted to rape her,&quot; Maya said, adding that she managed to save herself by running to another room.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Maya informed that she came to know about the incident only after the victim told a staff of NBA Laxmi Malla about the incident. He added that a complaint has been filed against Acharya at the district administration office Surkhet on November 24. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Inspector Rabin Karki of the district police office Surkhet said that search for the accused was on.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;em&gt;Durga Thapa&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Woman Complains of Police Inaction &lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Darchula/November 24&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An 18-year-woman of Amkur in Rithachaupata3 has complained that the police had failed to take action on her complaint of attempted rape against her even after four days of informing them. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;According to her, Krishna Singh Samant of Bhartola in Bhagwati1 had attempted to rape her on November 18 as she was going to her maternal house and that she managed to escape hitting him with stone. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;She said she went to District Police Office on November 20 but the police are yet to take any action.  Her husband Lalit Singh Bohora said the police had refused to register the FIR exerting pressure on his wife to settle the case in private. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The father of the accused, Dilip Singh claimed the incident was setteled after his son apologized. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The victim woman denied Dilip Singh's claim and added lack of action by the police had made her feel insecure. District Police Office said the accused was absconding since the incident and that they were investigating the case. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;em&gt;Narendra Singh Karki&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Girl Becomes Victim of Incestuous Rape &lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Bardiya/November 25&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A 6-year-old girl of Dhadhabar VDC has been raped by her own uncle, aged 24. The case has been reported at District Police Office, Bardiya and the police on November 24 arrested him and the investigation is going on. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Locals said the girl was raped in her house on November 23 where they found out. Police team of Area Police Office, Motipur, took the girl to the doctor.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;DPO's SI Kalpana Rana said the case was filed on November 25 and medical tests of the girl were conducted on Bardiya District Hospital . &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;em&gt;Man Bahadur Chaudhary&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
